;; Rename map: python-stdnum module keyword -> stdnum-clj type keyword.
;; stdnum-clj deliberately localizes many names (e.g. python's it/iva.py is our
;; :it-vat, us/rtn.py is our :aba, iso9362.py is our :bic, and python's `in_`/`is_`
;; reserved-word dirs are our plain `in`/`is`). Without this table the parity
;; watcher reports ~55 renames as false "missing types" every run.
;;
;; An entry here means "upstream module X is already covered by our type Y" — it is
;; subtracted from both the New-modules and the Not-upstream buckets. Country IBAN
;; modules all fold into the generic :iban.
;;
;; Maintenance: when you add a type that upstream names differently, add the pair
;; here. The watcher warns if a source is no longer an upstream module or a target
;; is no longer one of our types (stale alias).
{:at-uid           :at-vat
 :be-iban          :iban
 :be-ogm_vcs       :be-ogm
 :ca-bc_phn        :ca-bcphn
 :casrn            :cas
 :ch-ssn           :ch-ahv
